page.title: 01SUMMARY-LANDSCAPE-VILLAGES
page.content: SUMMARY of D Block This area is situated in the South west of Cambridgeshire and is mainly made up of farmland. It is largely arable land with few trees.Part of the area is raised above the valley of the River Ouse which runs though the east side of the area. Running parallel to the river is the main London to Scotland railway line.Running though the centre of the area is the B1043 road which goes from St Neots to Huntingdon.There are two villages_ Great Paxton to the south and Offord D'arcy to the north .Each village has a school and a church.Great Paxton has no shops now but Offord has one or two,so the nearest shopping towns are St Neots and Huntingdon.There is very little employment in the area.
